elections.description: Gillibrand, seeking a second full term, is an oft-mentioned presidential candidate.
Cuomo easily beat back a high-profile primary challenge from actress Cynthia Nixon in September.
Collins was indicted on insider-trading charges this summer. But President Trump won his western New York district with 60 percent of the vote, his best performance in the state.
Reed’s upstate district had been a battleground, but President Trump won it by 15 points in 2016.

Maloney, one of 13 Democrats representing a district President Trump won, is a candidate for state attorney general in a September primary and says he would abandon his House seat if he won the AG nomination.
Stefanik, a GOP rising star, represents a district President Trump won by 14 points in 2016 after voting Democratic in the previous two presidential elections.
Former President Obama won Zeldin's eastern Long Island district in both 2008 and 2012, but the seat shifted right in 2016, when President Trump carried it by 12 points.
Faso, a freshman, is facing Delgado in a seat President Trump carried by 7 points in 2016.
Katko has been resilient, but he's still running in a district Hillary Clinton carried by 4 points in 2016.
Donovan beat back a primary challenge from former Rep. Michael Grimm in June and is favored to win the general election in a district President Trump carried by 10 points in 2016.
President Trump won Tenney's district by more than 15 points, but Democrats consider Brindisi, a state assemblyman, a top recruit.
President Trump carried King's Long Island district by 9 points in 2016.
